Program: Last Word
Title: Albertina Sisulu, MF Husain, Patrick Leigh Fermor and John Mackenzie
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b011vjhm
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 19 Jun 2011
Jane Little on: Albertina Sisulu, whose contribution to the end of apartheid in South Africa led to her being called The Mother of the Nation. Adventurer, travel writer, and war hero Sir Patrick Leigh Fermor. TV and film director John MacKenzie, best known for The Long Good Friday. Carl Gardner, singer and founder of the 1950s hitmakers, The Coasters. And the 'Picasso of India', prolific artist MF Husein. Show less